it, chronology? Yeah. Of the development of the 
super... Which is a story that hasn't been written

09:41.500 --> 09:45.966
yet. Yeah. Well, one

09:46.657 --> 09:59.090
of the first things that happened was, of course, 
the whole business of a site. And the first money

10:00.211 --> 10:03.214
for that came from the governor's office. And that 
was to look at various sites. That was before the US

10:05.857 --> 10:15.567
Congress and the Department of Energy ever made 
the decision that we are going to go ahead and do a

10:05.857 --> 10:15.567
national search. what the guys here were pushing 
for was, we've got, we're working on the magnets,

10:16.694 --> 10:24.163
let's go find a site in Texas. And they got 
everybody, some of the people excited in the

10:24.664 --> 10:33.274
legislature, so they think at that time they came 
up with $400,000 to do a site study, six or seven

10:24.664 --> 10:33.274
sites. I don't know, Skip, give you the... I don't 
think we have to write it down, no, it's a search and

10:35.857 --> 10:38.481
sell. But you're right, that is an interesting 
story. And how... and how the universities work

10:45.787 --> 10:52.074
together on it is also, it's another volume. Yeah, 
I'm sure. You know how tough it is getting

10:54.216 --> 11:00.943
departments to work together in a single 
university.

